I am pretty sure there is a 1:1 correlation between enjoying and tolerating alcohol well and grip strength/neurological health. My buddy that I joke about being "old school" and drinking a lot can lift almost as much weight as me when we're both using Fat Grips on the pull lifts.

First two studies you find on this both immediately say there is a direct correlation between having good grip strength and drinking alcohol and one even suggests that alcohol may be protective against losing your grip strength with age. I don't think it's causative but it's real
Galkovsky calls it "Aquadespotism" and has some really nice articles trying to speculate about the psychology of people living under such a system

It's crazy that the Will Stancil guy presumably spent literal decades before all this just tweeting his policy proposals for adding more bike lanes to roads and posting selfies from protests against global warming. Then next day he's defending himself from a rape fiction chatbot.

Illustrates what Contrary Pancake said about the "Online Right" being a circus that comes to town to abolish normal life and replace it with a permanent carnival. This same man now has dozens of involuntary inside jokes with a bunch of rightwing trolls. The carnival overtook him.
